  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7036.82 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive +11957M gamma wall at 7050, dealers are likely covering short delta from the recent 9.7% move while preparing to aggressively sell into any push toward 7050. The PIN regime with strong positive gamma walls above suggests dealers will provide heavy resistance at 7050-7100, creating a natural ceiling for price action. Key levels to watch are the 7015 negative gamma floor (dealer buying support) and the 7050 wall where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 7015-7050 with choppy action as dealers defend these boundaries.",
